HEADWORD: Peccavi
<hw>Pec*ca"vi</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <ety>[L.]</ety> <def>I have sinned;
-- used colloquially to express confession or acknowledgment of an
offense; -- used rarely, superseded by the approximate equivalent
<altname>mea culpa</altname>.</def> <rj><au>Aubrey.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pecco</ent>⟦br⟧
